      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/3x-more-omega-3-in-eggs-if-pasture-raised/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;well-being-eggs---dr-malone&#34;&gt;Well Being: Eggs - Dr. Malone&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://rwmalonemd.substack.com/p/well-being-eggs?utm_campaign=email-post&amp;amp;r=ofo3r&amp;amp;utm_source=substack&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&#34;&gt;Substack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The USDA’s (and industry standards’) definition for “Free Range” is that birds must have “outdoor access” or “access to the outdoors.”  In some cases, this can mean access only through a “pop hole,” with  &lt;strong&gt;no full-body access to the outdoors&lt;/strong&gt;  and no minimum space requirement. Basically a hole in the wall - from which they can stick their heads out of. Sort of.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
